<div class="main_body_subhead orng_text">Kroogi Widget Tutorial</div>

Kroogi has a widget that allows you to easily share and promote your music. Using an HTML code, you can embed albums into a web page (provided they support HTML).<br /><br />

If you're an artist, this is a great way to promote your work. If you're a fan, you can use the widget to support your favorite musicians by sharing their music with others.<br /><br />

<a href="http://community.livejournal.com/kroogi_news/2542.html" target="_blank">Here's what it looks like</a><br /><br />

<b>How to use it:</b><br /><br />

1. Go to a Kroogi artist profile.<br /><br />
2. Click on the album that you want to share.<br /><br />
3. On the left-hand side of the page, underneath the Download button, there's a button titled "Embed This." Click it.<br /><br />
4. A box will pop up with the embed code at the top. Copy and paste it into a website to display the widget.<br /><br /><br />

<b>How it works:</b><br /><br />

1. People can play music directly from the widget, by clicking on the play symbol next to each track.<br /><br />
2. On the upper right hand side of the widget, there is a "Download this album" button. When clicked, it will direct viewers to the album's Kroogi page.<br /><br />




